    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-04-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-04-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="1611"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1611">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.93/71.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Hamm</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Durango</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 24, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Chinese this city fearful and desire leave. Is it prohibitory grant them
                    temporary asylum in the United States and will Chinese Legation Washington
                    reimburse me for money advanced for transportation of deserving Chinese?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hamm</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
